The film reveals the incredible and varied human stories of the passengers involved,
and the terror and exhilaration that accompany a
near-death experience. On 15 January 2009, 155 people on board US Airways
flight 1549 faced their worst nightmare. Just two minutes into the flight,
a flock of birds struck the plane, taking out both engines. 
With no power, Captain Chesley Sullenberger decided he had only one option:
 to land in the Hudson River. Miracle on the Hudson tells the 
minute-by-minute story of that day through the compelling first-hand 
testimonies of those who were there, including passengers, 
eyewitnesses and rescuers, with exclusive interviews and videos.
